rComments: Prof. Anya is very knowledgeable and accessible outside class. She holds plenty of office hours, cares about students' mental health, makes sure we understand the material, gives us plenty of time to ask questions, and tries her best to help students learn without overwhelming us with work. Also, her lectures are super interesting and never boring.

She's the GOAT. Uploaded our final exam on crowdmark so we didn't have to pay to see it. When there was a mistake regarding marking, she made sure students never lost marks over this and only gained marks once the mistake was corrected. Extremely approachable and active on Piazza.
teacherRatingTags: ['Caring', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Anya is amazing, her lectures are always interesting and never dry and boring. She also provides lots of help, she has 20+ office hours in total scheduled per week (her & TAs). The assignments really make you think and checks your understanding of the material. Her tests are fair if you studied. The one con is that she missed quite a few lectures.

She was really nice and would spend time outside of class helping us with different things. She seemed like she really cared that we understood the material and gave us lots of help if needed. She also made the lectures interesting.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Severe punctuality issues on top of empty promises. Poor course design, just awful. Promises the release marks and assignments within a certain timeframe, this never came true and it wasn't even close. An astounding amount of ambiguity in her assignments. Multiple choice is the hardest part of her exams. Pure factoids very little application.
Anya is doing a great job teaching us first years. She explains concepts clearly, very caring for her students, and just a nice prof overall.
She was a really great prof . Definitely recommend her class
Felt way too much work at the time, but now I see it was pretty much the only useful course they taught.

An amazing professor who really knows her stuff. I can understand if not everyone likes her. She gives pretty tight deadlines, but it does ensure that you are prepared for upper years and working in the industry. She is really nice.
BEAWARE! She gives A LOT of stuff to do on when you least expect it! Plan your time wisely!
She could not explain anything clearly but she gives very hard tests.

C24 is inherently a fast course. We learnt Scheme, Haskell, and Prolog. Prolog was very short and a bit abrupt. Most of the time spent was on Haskell which is one of the important languages in functional programming. We also went back to Python and Java and related the concepts being learnt to these languages. This course make you think!
This professor was pretty good in CSCA20.  Picky in terms of grading in certain assessments.  Other than that, she's a pretty lenient prof
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Anya is very helpful but she was pretty much flying through all her lectures in order to cover everything. One of our projects was to make an android app. A lot of this course is just SELF-STUDY. My advice to anyone taking this course with Anya: PRACTICE ALL HER CODES AFTER EACH LECTURE. She is Nice but not Easy.
The stuff you learn in the class is such a bore, Anya doesn't make it less  boring. She expects a lot and you have to learn almost everything yourself.

She's so so so strict, if you got mark lower than 50 in your assignment, you will probably get 0 in the end. Also, if you choose the wrong answer of multiple choose in the final exam, you will get -1 mark!!!
I felt she was unorganized in her lectures. She is very strict when it comes to the assignments: either you do *everything correctly* or pay heavily. No pity whatsoever. Do not take her ligthly.
